cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on distributed graph computing systems and proposes techniques to improve their performance, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with large graphs and proposes algorithms to reduce the number of messages exchanged, which is a key aspect of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions online social networks and communication networks as examples of massive graphs, which are studied under this sub-category. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the communication bottleneck in distributed graph computing systems, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper proposes techniques to reduce the number of messages exchanged in distributed graph computation, which can improve the performance of graph databases.
